<h2 class="title">Choropleth maps with R</h2>
<p>Examples of plotting region-level data on country maps using the <a href="http://docs.ggplot2.org/current/">ggplot2</a> package and shape files from <a href="http://gadm.org">gadm.org</a>.</p>
<hr />
<div id="overview" class="section level4">
<h4>Overview</h4>
<ol style="list-style-type: decimal">
<li><a href="#I">Simulated data for Norwegian communes</a><br />
</li>
<li><a href="#II">Region-level literacy data from Ghanaian census</a></li>
</ol>
<hr />
<p>Start by installing the following packages.</p>
<pre class="r"><code>## load packages
install.packages(&quot;raster&quot;)
install.packages(&quot;ggplot2&quot;)
install.packages(&quot;rgeos&quot;)
install.packages(&quot;maptools&quot;)
install.packages(&quot;scales&quot;)</code></pre>
<hr />
</div>
<div id="simulated-data-for-norwegian-communes" class="section level4">
<h4><a name="I"></a> 1. Simulated data for Norwegian communes</h4>
<pre class="r"><code>## download shapefile from gadm.org level=1 -&gt; region ; level=2 -&gt; commune
library(raster)
states.shp &lt;- getData(&quot;GADM&quot;, country = &quot;NOR&quot;, level = 2)
class(states.shp)</code></pre>
<pre><code>## [1] &quot;SpatialPolygonsDataFrame&quot;
## attr(,&quot;package&quot;)
## [1] &quot;sp&quot;</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>names(states.shp)</code></pre>
<pre><code>##  [1] &quot;OBJECTID&quot;  &quot;ID_0&quot;      &quot;ISO&quot;       &quot;NAME_0&quot;    &quot;ID_1&quot;     
##  [6] &quot;NAME_1&quot;    &quot;ID_2&quot;      &quot;NAME_2&quot;    &quot;HASC_2&quot;    &quot;CCN_2&quot;    
## [11] &quot;CCA_2&quot;     &quot;TYPE_2&quot;    &quot;ENGTYPE_2&quot; &quot;NL_NAME_2&quot; &quot;VARNAME_2&quot;</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>head(states.shp$NAME_2)</code></pre>
<pre><code>## [1] &quot;Aremark&quot;     &quot;Askim&quot;       &quot;Borge&quot;       &quot;Eidsberg&quot;    &quot;Fredrikstad&quot;
## [6] &quot;Halden&quot;</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>## fortify shape file to dataframe format
library(rgeos)
library(maptools)
library(ggplot2)
states.shp.f &lt;- fortify(states.shp, region = &quot;NAME_2&quot;)
class(states.shp.f)</code></pre>
<pre><code>## [1] &quot;data.frame&quot;</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>head(states.shp.f)</code></pre>
<pre><code>##       long      lat order  hole piece     id    group
## 1 10.44185 63.75298     1 FALSE     1 Åfjord Åfjord.1
## 2 10.44034 63.75742     2 FALSE     1 Åfjord Åfjord.1
## 3 10.43884 63.76186     3 FALSE     1 Åfjord Åfjord.1
## 4 10.43734 63.76630     4 FALSE     1 Åfjord Åfjord.1
## 5 10.43583 63.77074     5 FALSE     1 Åfjord Åfjord.1
## 6 10.43433 63.77519     6 FALSE     1 Åfjord Åfjord.1</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>## create random data to plot on map
num.states &lt;- length(states.shp$NAME_2)
set.seed(123)
mydata &lt;- data.frame(id = states.shp$NAME_2, prevalence = rnorm(num.states, 
    55, 20))
head(mydata)</code></pre>
<pre><code>##            id prevalence
## 1     Aremark   43.79049
## 2       Askim   50.39645
## 3       Borge   86.17417
## 4    Eidsberg   56.41017
## 5 Fredrikstad   57.58575
## 6      Halden   89.30130</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>## merge shape file with data
merge.shp.coef &lt;- merge(states.shp.f, mydata, by = &quot;id&quot;)
head(merge.shp.coef)</code></pre>
<pre><code>##       id     long      lat order  hole piece    group prevalence
## 1 Åfjord 10.44185 63.75298     1 FALSE     1 Åfjord.1   69.07048
## 2 Åfjord 10.44034 63.75742     2 FALSE     1 Åfjord.1   69.07048
## 3 Åfjord 10.43884 63.76186     3 FALSE     1 Åfjord.1   69.07048
## 4 Åfjord 10.43734 63.76630     4 FALSE     1 Åfjord.1   69.07048
## 5 Åfjord 10.43583 63.77074     5 FALSE     1 Åfjord.1   69.07048
## 6 Åfjord 10.43433 63.77519     6 FALSE     1 Åfjord.1   69.07048</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>## basic plot
ggplot() + geom_polygon(data = merge.shp.coef, aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group, 
    fill = prevalence), color = &quot;black&quot;, size = 0.25) + coord_map()</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," title alt width="672" style="display: block; margin: auto;" /></p>
<pre class="r"><code>## nicer plot
library(scales)
library(ggmap)
ggplot() + geom_polygon(data = merge.shp.coef, aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group, 
    fill = prevalence), color = &quot;black&quot;, size = 0.25) + coord_map() + scale_fill_distiller(name = &quot;prevalence&quot;, 
    palette = &quot;YlGn&quot;, breaks = pretty_breaks(n = 5)) + theme_nothing(legend = TRUE) + 
    labs(title = &quot;Prevalence of X in Norway&quot;)</code></pre>
<p><img src="data:image/png;base64," title alt width="672" style="display: block; margin: auto;" /></p>
<p><a href="#">Back to top</a></p>

<div id="region-level-literacy-data-from-ghanaian-census" class="section level4">
<h4><a name="II"></a> 2. Region-level literacy data from Ghanaian census</h4>
<p>Now, let us try to use the above code snippets to produce regional-level plots for Ghana based on the 2010 census. Take the literacy rate as an example.</p>
<pre class="r"><code>## read individual-level literacy data from 2010 census
load(url(&quot;http://klein.uk/R/Viz/litGH.RData&quot;))

## drop population below 11 age
litGH &lt;- litGH[litGH$LITERACY != &quot;Less than 11&quot;, ]

## define binary literacy variable
litGH$literacy &lt;- ifelse(litGH$LITERACY == &quot;None (Not literate)&quot;, 0, 1)
litGH$id &lt;- litGH$REGION

## obtain region-level literacy rates
(litGH &lt;- aggregate(formula = literacy ~ id, data = litGH, FUN = mean))</code></pre>
<pre><code>##               id  literacy
## 1        Western 0.7646089
## 2        Central 0.7809877
## 3  Greater Accra 0.8930270
## 4          Volta 0.7350536
## 5        Eastern 0.8113143
## 6        Ashanti 0.8276943
## 7    Brong Ahafo 0.6979829
## 8       Northern 0.3715225
## 9     Upper East 0.4757000
## 10    Upper West 0.4646903</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>mydata &lt;- litGH</code></pre>
<p>Start over from 1. to download the shapefiles for Ghana (ISO code <code>'GHA'</code>) and produce the choropleth maps. Note: make sure to use regional levels, i.e. <code>level = 1</code> and <code>NAME_1</code>, instead of the commune-level variables in the Norwegian data above.</p>
<pre class="r"><code>## download shapefile from gadm.org level=1 -&gt; region ; level=2 -&gt; commune
library(raster)
states.shp &lt;- getData(&quot;GADM&quot;, country = &quot;GHA&quot;, level = 1)
class(states.shp)</code></pre>
<pre><code>## [1] &quot;SpatialPolygonsDataFrame&quot;
## attr(,&quot;package&quot;)
## [1] &quot;sp&quot;</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>names(states.shp)</code></pre>
<pre><code>##  [1] &quot;OBJECTID&quot;  &quot;ID_0&quot;      &quot;ISO&quot;       &quot;NAME_0&quot;    &quot;ID_1&quot;     
##  [6] &quot;NAME_1&quot;    &quot;HASC_1&quot;    &quot;CCN_1&quot;     &quot;CCA_1&quot;     &quot;TYPE_1&quot;   
## [11] &quot;ENGTYPE_1&quot; &quot;NL_NAME_1&quot; &quot;VARNAME_1&quot;</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>states.shp$NAME_1</code></pre>
<pre><code>##  [1] &quot;Ashanti&quot;       &quot;Brong Ahafo&quot;   &quot;Central&quot;       &quot;Eastern&quot;      
##  [5] &quot;Greater Accra&quot; &quot;Northern&quot;      &quot;Upper East&quot;    &quot;Upper West&quot;   
##  [9] &quot;Volta&quot;         &quot;Western&quot;</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>## fortify shape file to dataframe format
library(rgeos)
library(maptools)
library(ggplot2)
states.shp.f &lt;- fortify(states.shp, region = &quot;NAME_1&quot;)
class(states.shp.f)</code></pre>
<pre><code>## [1] &quot;data.frame&quot;</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>head(states.shp.f)</code></pre>
<pre><code>##        long      lat order  hole piece      id     group
## 1 -1.260922 7.456426     1 FALSE     1 Ashanti Ashanti.1
## 2 -1.253900 7.456198     2 FALSE     1 Ashanti Ashanti.1
## 3 -1.236103 7.456228     3 FALSE     1 Ashanti Ashanti.1
## 4 -1.229099 7.456490     4 FALSE     1 Ashanti Ashanti.1
## 5 -1.225717 7.456898     5 FALSE     1 Ashanti Ashanti.1
## 6 -1.222512 7.457714     6 FALSE     1 Ashanti Ashanti.1</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>## merge shape file with data
merge.shp.coef &lt;- merge(states.shp.f, mydata, by = &quot;id&quot;)
head(merge.shp.coef)</code></pre>
<pre><code>##        id      long      lat order  hole piece     group  literacy
## 1 Ashanti -1.260922 7.456426     1 FALSE     1 Ashanti.1 0.8276943
## 2 Ashanti -1.253900 7.456198     2 FALSE     1 Ashanti.1 0.8276943
## 3 Ashanti -1.236103 7.456228     3 FALSE     1 Ashanti.1 0.8276943
## 4 Ashanti -1.229099 7.456490     4 FALSE     1 Ashanti.1 0.8276943
## 5 Ashanti -1.225717 7.456898     5 FALSE     1 Ashanti.1 0.8276943
## 6 Ashanti -1.222512 7.457714     6 FALSE     1 Ashanti.1 0.8276943</code></pre>
<pre class="r"><code>## basic plot
ggplot() + geom_polygon(data = merge.shp.coef, aes(x = long, y = lat, group = group, 
    fill = literacy), color = &quot;black&quot;, size = 0.25) + coord_map()</code></pre>
